I"µ<p>The Secure Shell (<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ssh</code>) is a popular tool for remotely accessing and working with servers or computers. There are other ways to do this, but as the name suggests, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ssh</code> automatically encrypts data sent over the network, providing a private and secure connection. It has become the chosen tool for remote connections.</p>
